Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

DOS-PORT (patch 0033, Phase 9 wave 17.4).

Pre-patch: DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer's three pitches_match
branches (single-bank dosmemput, multi-bank BankedDosmemput, nearptr
LFB SDL_memcpy) IGNORED the rect list and pushed the entire fb_size
to VRAM unconditionally. Only the !pitches_match branches honored
rects (per-rect dosmemput / SDL_memcpy with bank switching).

This defeated SDL_UpdateWindowSurfaceRects callers that wanted
partial flush — including the wave-15 nxengine engine when its
dirty-rect list was small enough to bypass the threshold check. The
engine layer correctly chose the partial path; the SDL layer flushed
the whole frame anyway.

This patch fixes the three pitches_match branches to:

1. Use the existing full-fb fast path (dosmemput / BankedDosmemput /
   SDL_memcpy of fb_state.fb_size in one shot) ONLY when the rect
   list represents a full-screen flush (single rect with x=0, y=0,
   w >= vram_w, h >= vram_h). This is the common case from
   SDL_UpdateWindowSurface, which constructs a single full-window
   rect before calling UpdateWindowSurfaceRects.

2. Otherwise dispatch to a per-rect loop that honors the partial
   list. Inside the loop, when pitches match AND the rect spans the
   full row width (rx=0, rw==vram_w), do a single contiguous
   dosmemput / BankedDosmemput / SDL_memcpy of (rh × src_pitch)
   bytes — bypasses the per-row inner loop. Engine prev-frame diff
   (companion patch nxengine/0082) produces full-row band rects, so
   this fast path is the common case post-wave-17.4.

3. Otherwise (pitches don't match OR rect is sub-row width) fall
   back to per-row dosmemput as before.

Helper added: _doskutsu_is_full_fb_rect_list — single-rect
full-screen-coverage check, called once per dispatch.

No behavioral change in the !pitches_match branches.
No regression for full-screen flushes (existing fast path still fires).
The new per-rect partial path delivers the win when the engine sends
small rects.

This is a doskutsu-local patch; it's not upstreamed (per the doskutsu
CLAUDE.md no-upstream policy and the user's sdl_ai_policy memory).
---
 src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c | 80 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 76 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c
index 3486258c1..0f078e230 100644
--- a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c
+++ b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c
@@ -84,6 +84,28 @@ static DOSFramebufferState fb_state;
 static Uint32 _dbg_bank_switches_total = 0;
 static Uint32 _dbg_bytes_written_total = 0;
 
+// DOSKUTSU patch 0033 (wave 17.4): partial-flush detector. The engine
+// passes a rect list to UpdateWindowFramebuffer; the wave-15 dirty-rect
+// fast path passes small rects when only a sub-region of the frame
+// changed (after the wave-17.4 nxengine patch 0082 prev-frame diff
+// produces real partial-flush rect lists). Pre-patch, the pitches_match
+// branches in this file ignored the rect list and dosmemput'd the
+// entire fb_size — defeating partial flush. This helper detects the
+// "single full-screen rect" case, which is the SDL_UpdateWindowSurface
+// path's behavior (it constructs a single rect covering the whole
+// window). When that's what we got, the existing full-fb fast path is
+// optimal. When numrects > 1 OR the rect is sub-screen, switch to the
+// per-rect path with a row-contiguous optimization for pitches_match.
+static bool _doskutsu_is_full_fb_rect_list(const SDL_Rect *rects,
+                                            int numrects,
+                                            int vw, int vh)
+{
+    if (numrects != 1) return false;
+    return rects[0].x <= 0 && rects[0].y <= 0 &&
+           rects[0].x + rects[0].w >= vw &&
+           rects[0].y + rects[0].h >= vh;
+}
+
 // Convert cursor to the current format.
 static SDL_Surface *GetConvertedCursorSurface(SDL_CursorData *curdata, SDL_Surface *dst)
 {
@@ -954,8 +976,17 @@ bool DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer(SDL_VideoDevice *device, SDL_Window *window
 
             if (!fb_state.banked_multibank) {
                 // Single-bank: entire FB fits in one window (e.g. mode 13h).
-                // Full-surface fast path when pitches match.
-                if (fb_state.pitches_match) {
+                //
+                // DOS-PORT (patch 0033, wave 17.4): partial-flush dispatch.
+                // Full-surface fast path when pitches match AND the rect
+                // list represents a full-screen flush (single rect spanning
+                // the mode dimensions). Otherwise per-rect dosmemput, with
+                // a row-contiguous optimization that bulk-copies a full-
+                // width rect band as one dosmemput when pitches match.
+                if (fb_state.pitches_match &&
+                    _doskutsu_is_full_fb_rect_list(rects, numrects,
+                                                   fb_state.vram_w,
+                                                   fb_state.vram_h)) {
                     dosmemput(pixels, fb_state.fb_size, fb_state.vram_phys);
                 } else {
                     for (int i = 0; i < numrects; i++) {
@@ -978,6 +1009,16 @@ bool DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer(SDL_VideoDevice *device, SDL_Window *window
                         if (rw <= 0 || rh <= 0) {
                             continue;
                         }
+                        // DOS-PORT (patch 0033, wave 17.4): bulk row-contiguous
+                        // dosmemput when pitches match and rect spans full row.
+                        // Engine prev-frame diff produces full-width row bands,
+                        // so this fast path is the common case post-patch 0082.
+                        if (fb_state.pitches_match && rx == 0 && rw == fb_state.vram_w) {
+                            dosmemput(pixels + ry * src_pitch,
+                                      (Uint32)rh * (Uint32)src_pitch,
+                                      fb_state.vram_phys + ry * dst_pitch);
+                            continue;
+                        }
                         const int bx = rx * fb_state.bpp;
                         const int bw = rw * fb_state.bpp;
                         const Uint8 *sp = pixels + ry * src_pitch + bx;
@@ -997,7 +1038,12 @@ bool DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer(SDL_VideoDevice *device, SDL_Window *window
                 const Uint32 wfunc = fb_state.win_func_ptr;
                 int current_bank = -1;
 
-                if (fb_state.pitches_match) {
+                // DOS-PORT (patch 0033, wave 17.4): partial-flush dispatch
+                // for multi-bank, mirroring the single-bank branch above.
+                if (fb_state.pitches_match &&
+                    _doskutsu_is_full_fb_rect_list(rects, numrects,
+                                                   fb_state.vram_w,
+                                                   fb_state.vram_h)) {
                     // Contiguous: stream the entire framebuffer through banks.
                     BankedDosmemput(pixels, fb_state.fb_size, 0,
                                     gran, wsize, wbase, wfunc, &current_bank);
@@ -1023,6 +1069,18 @@ bool DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer(SDL_VideoDevice *device, SDL_Window *window
                         if (rw <= 0 || rh <= 0) {
                             continue;
                         }
+                        // DOS-PORT (patch 0033, wave 17.4): row-contiguous
+                        // bulk BankedDosmemput when pitches match and rect
+                        // spans full row — band shaped rects from the engine
+                        // prev-frame diff (patch 0082) hit this branch.
+                        if (fb_state.pitches_match && rx == 0 && rw == fb_state.vram_w) {
+                            Uint32 dst_offset = (Uint32)ry * dst_pitch;
+                            BankedDosmemput(pixels + ry * src_pitch,
+                                            (Uint32)rh * (Uint32)src_pitch,
+                                            dst_offset,
+                                            gran, wsize, wbase, wfunc, &current_bank);
+                            continue;
+                        }
                         const int bx = rx * fb_state.bpp;
                         const int bw = rw * fb_state.bpp;
 
@@ -1037,7 +1095,13 @@ bool DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer(SDL_VideoDevice *device, SDL_Window *window
             }
         } else {
             // nearptr path (LFB fallback)
-            if (fb_state.pitches_match) {
+            //
+            // DOS-PORT (patch 0033, wave 17.4): partial-flush dispatch
+            // for the nearptr LFB path, mirroring the dosmemput branches.
+            if (fb_state.pitches_match &&
+                _doskutsu_is_full_fb_rect_list(rects, numrects,
+                                                fb_state.vram_w,
+                                                fb_state.vram_h)) {
                 SDL_memcpy(fb_state.vram_ptr, fb_state.pixels, fb_state.fb_size);
             } else {
                 const int bpp = fb_state.bpp;
@@ -1065,6 +1129,14 @@ bool DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer(SDL_VideoDevice *device, SDL_Window *window
                     if (rw <= 0 || rh <= 0) {
                         continue;
                     }
+                    // DOS-PORT (patch 0033, wave 17.4): contiguous bulk
+                    // memcpy when pitches match and rect spans full row.
+                    if (fb_state.pitches_match && rx == 0 && rw == fb_state.vram_w) {
+                        SDL_memcpy(fb_state.vram_ptr + ry * dst_pitch,
+                                   pixels + ry * src_pitch,
+                                   (size_t)rh * (size_t)src_pitch);
+                        continue;
+                    }
                     const int bw = rw * bpp;
                     const Uint8 *sp = pixels + ry * src_pitch + rx * bpp;
                     Uint8 *dp = fb_state.vram_ptr + ry * dst_pitch + rx * bpp;
